com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Class SeriesFlags

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec.SeriesFlags

  • public class SeriesFlags
extends java.lang.Object
    A combination of bit values that indicates the presence of optional Series content.
    See Also:
    Series

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int HAS_SET_DEFS
      (0x01) Indicates that the Series contains local set definition information.
      static int HAS_SUMMARY_DATA
      (0x02) Indicates that the Series contains summary data.
      static int HAS_TOTAL_COUNT_HINT
      (0x04) Indicates the presence of the totalCountHint member, which can provide an approximation of the total number of entries sent across maps on all parts of the refresh message.
      static int NONE
      (0x00) None of the optional flags are present.

    • Field Detail

      • NONE

        public static final int NONE
        (0x00) None of the optional flags are present.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • HAS_SET_DEFS

        public static final int HAS_SET_DEFS
        (0x01) Indicates that the Series contains local set definition information. Local set definitions correspond to data contained in this Series's entries and encode or decode their contents.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • HAS_SUMMARY_DATA

        public static final int HAS_SUMMARY_DATA
        (0x02) Indicates that the Series contains summary data.
        • If set while encoding, summary data must be provided by encoding or populating encodedSummaryData with pre-encoded information.
        • If set while decoding, summary data is contained as part of Series and the user can choose to decode it.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • HAS_TOTAL_COUNT_HINT

        public static final int HAS_TOTAL_COUNT_HINT
        (0x04) Indicates the presence of the totalCountHint member, which can provide an approximation of the total number of entries sent across maps on all parts of the refresh message. Such information is useful when determining resource allocation for caching or displaying all expected entries.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
